TISTICAL SAMPLING OF REFERENCE DESK INQUIRIES.DISCUSSES THE APPLICATION OF STATISTICAL SAMPLING TO THE COMPILING OFREFERENCE DESK STATISTICS. DESCRIBES A TECHNIQUE THAT USES THE PEARSONCORRELATION PROCEDURE OF SPSS (STATISTICAL PACKAGE FOR THE SOCIAL SCIENCES) TODETERMINE APPROPRIATE SAMPLING PERIODS FOR KEEPING REFERENCE DESK STATISTICSAT THE UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI AT ST. LOUIS. COVERS RESULTS AND IMPLICATIONS OFTHE FINDINGS, INCLUDING POTENTIAL APPLICATION OF THE PROCEDURE TO OTHERLIBRARY SITUATIONS